East London medical doctor, Dr Siphokazi Sokupa will spend the weekend behind bars after her bail application was postponed to Monday. Sokupa appeared at the East London magistrate's court on Friday, National Prosecuting Authority regional spokesperson, Anelisa Ngcakani confirmed. "The matter was postponed to Monday, 1 June 2020 for the continuation of the bail application," she said in a statement on Friday night. The 67 year-old has two pending cases which are before court. The other two pending cases are for fraud after she allegedly issued medical certificates to an undercover officer while this year she was charged with allegedly fraud, corruption and contravening the disaster management act. It is the state's case that Sokupa allegedly issued medical certificates to taxi drivers. In her April 4 sworn affidavit, Sokupa indicated she would plead not guilty to all charges.